	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/livy/liv.per106.shtml
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Livy, <I>Epit.</I> 106
	</A>
and
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#26
	"TARGET="Suetonius_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EPlusL,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Suet. <I>Caes.</I> 26</A>.
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cassius_Dio/39*.html#64
	"TARGET="Cassius_Dio_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Dio,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Dio <SPAN CLASS="small">XXXIX</SPAN>.64
	</A>
says "daughter."

	<DIV CLASS="mynote">
	<P CLASS="b0 a0">
Thayer's Note: Both Livy and Suetonius, as given online, have "daughter" as well. The online text of the Epitome of Livy is from an unspecified edition; both online texts of Suetonius are that of Ihm's edition of 1907, picked up by the Loeb edition with no critical note <I>ad loc.</I>, which, published in 1913, predates the Loeb edition of Velleius on this page by 11 years.
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note137" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref137
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">137</A>
52 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note138" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref138
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">138</A>
52 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN><!-- identical with preceding note -->


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note139" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref139
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">139</A>
55 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note140" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref140
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">140</A>
About £100,000 or $500,000.

	<DIV CLASS="mynoteWide">
Thayer's Note: A reminder that this equivalent dates to 1924 (notice the pound at $5); in 2003, the figure would be about $5,000,000 or £3,200,000.
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note141" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref141
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">141</A>
49 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note142" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref142
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">142</A>
Probably refers to Caesar's offer
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Appian/Civil_Wars/2*.html#32
	"TARGET="Appian_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Appian,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(App. <I>B. C.</I> <SPAN CLASS="small">II</SPAN>.32)
	</A>
to be satisfied with Cisalpine Gaul and Illyria, with <I>two</I> legions.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note143" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref143
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">143</A>
Jan. 12 or 13, 49 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note144" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref144
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">144</A>
At Ilerda, August, 49 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note145" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref145
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">145</A>
48 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note146" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref146
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">146</A>
Described in
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Caesar/Civil_Wars/3C*.html#62
	"TARGET="Caesar_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,1,WIDTH,165)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Caes. <I>Bell. Civ.</I> <SPAN CLASS="small">III</SPAN>.62‑70</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note147" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref147
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">147</A>
August 9, 48 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note148" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref148
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">148</A>
See note on text<!--</A>-->. The general sense is supplied from


<A ID="p165x"></A><SPAN CLASS="pagenum">(p165)</SPAN>the account in
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#75
	"TARGET="Suetonius_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EPlusL,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Suet. <I>Caes.</I> 75
	</A>
and
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Appian/Civil_Wars/2*.html#80
	"TARGET="Appian_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Appian,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Appian, <I>Bellum Civile</I> ii.80</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note149" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref149
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">149</A>
Caesar,
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/caesar/bc3.shtml#104
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>Bell. Civ.</I> <SPAN CLASS="small">III</SPAN>.104</A>,<A CLASS="correction"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(CarelessLoeb80+'<I>Bell. Civ.</I> 104</SPAN>',WIDTH,120)"
onMouseOut="nd();">º</A> says it was a "<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">navicula parvula</SPAN>."


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note150" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref150
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">150</A>
48 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note151" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref151
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">151</A>
Consuls 106 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note152" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref152
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">152</A>
Cato had held the <SPAN CLASS="whole">praetor</SPAN>&shy;ship only.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note153" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref153
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">153</A>
At Thapsus, April 6, 46.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note154" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref154
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">154</A>
At Zela, in 47 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> It is here mentioned out of its proper order.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note155" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref155
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">155</A>
Battle of Munda, March 17, 45 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note156" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref156
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">156</A>
The first four in 46 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>, the Spanish triumph in 45 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note157" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref157
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">157</A>
About £5,500,000 or $27,000,000.

	<DIV CLASS="mynoteWide">
Thayer's Note: in 2003, about $270,000,000 or £170,000,000.
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note158" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref158
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">158</A>
March 15, 44 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note159" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref159
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">159</A>
Usually of <SPAN CLASS="whole">Etruscan</SPAN> origin, who professed ability to foretell the future from the examination of the entrails of sacrificial animals.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note160" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref160
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">160</A>
<I>i.e.</I> on his contemplated departure for the Parthian expedition.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note161" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref161
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">161</A>
It may be that Velleius means simply "son" as was indeed the fact, and that <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">liberos</SPAN> is a rhetorical plural like that in
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/cicero/phil1.shtml#2
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Cic. <I>Phil.</I> <SPAN CLASS="small">I</SPAN>.1.1</A>. It is clear from
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/cicero/phil1.shtml#31
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>Phil.</I> <SPAN CLASS="small">I</SPAN>.13.31
	</A>
that Cicero is referring to but one.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note162" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref162
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">162</A>
When the Thirty Tyrants were overthrown and democracy was restored under Thrasybulus.



	<HR CLASS="endnotes"><A ID="endnotes_T"></A>
	<H2>
Thayer's Notes:
	</H2>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note:army_from_Picenum" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref:army_from_Picenum
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">a</A>
Or possibly, "an army from the area of Firmum, in the district of Picenum"
	<A HREF="
L/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#note:firmum
	"TARGET="Velleius"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,1,WIDTH,165)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(see my critical note)</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note:not_pontifex_maximus" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Velleius_Paterculus/2B*.html#ref:not_pontifex_maximus
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">b</A>
Here the Loeb translator has <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">pontifex maximus</SPAN> — a slip, since Caesar's early attainment of that dignity, remarkable enough as it was, was more than ten years in the future. <I>Kudos for the good catch to Birte Bronger.</I>



